4: Seeya, Mr. Kengyu! Have a good night!
16:

You guys sure tired him out!
21:
Yup. He was up against super wrestlers 
like you, after all. You'll have plenty of 
time to play tomorrow.
23:
He has to do the tiger driver! 
The move that's all like GRAAWR and 
then FWOOOSH and BAM!
27:

take one for the team!
32:
Whew. Where do they get so much 
energy?

40:

much...

once in a while.
45:
Your help would always be most 
welcome.

your eye?
My late wife, Iori.
59:
I'm sorry for your loss.
I didn't mean to stare...
62:

seen, after all.
65:
An old friend of ours—an excellent

of her.
...I am eternally grateful he did.
69:
I see...
It's beautiful work. She was lovely...
72:
She truly was. She was even more 
beautiful in person!
75:
Ahaha, she must have been, to have 
you so head over heels.
80:
I could speak of her for days. You must 
have your fair share of stories too Light.
 I may have just the thing to talk the 
night away.
84:
A bottle of Unryu's finest. I was saving 
it for an occasion such as this. 
What do you say, friend?
92: Come, let us sit and share old memories.
96: Gladly! How could I say no?
102:
I'll... save ymm... 
Mm... Prin... Lily...
106:
He certainly keeps a lot bottled away 
in that little body of his.
108:
Though tough as he may be, I suppose 
the drink may have won this match.
110: Ungh... no... mmn... not the ears...
119:
The days are so warm and bright, and 
yet... They weigh so heavily on my 
heart.
122:
Perhaps it is because they remind me 
of my time with you, Iori.
